            <atom:updated>2018-12-07T04:13:08.217Z</atom:updated>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h4><strong>What is Crash？</strong></h4><p>CRASH is an online betting game, displaying as an increasing curve that may collapse at any time.</p><h4>How to Play it？</h4><p>Before the game starts, you have 6 seconds to place your bet. After the game starts, the multiples will get higher and higher starting from 1X. Click on “Escape” at any time to lock your current multiples, and your earnings will be your bet times the current multiple.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*-s1khI5Kn3I3jrmCZmLxdQ.jpeg" /></figure><p>Escape at 1.01x, 100x, 1000x or 10000x…? It’s all up to you — just a split of a second! (This game is not for the weak-hearted).</p><h4>Is this a fair game?（ Found unfair, rewarding 100 ETH）</h4><p>Provably fair bets with 1% edge.</p><p>10 million hashes are generated and released in reverse order (the generation chain is verifiable), each of which corresponding to a curve crash number, meaning that we have 10 million turns in total.</p><p>In other words, the long-established crash number for each turn is not calculated at the beginning of the game, assuring the fairness.</p><h4>Is this game manipulated by our platform?</h4><p>Impossible manipulation. Please check github for more information.</p><p><a href="https://github.com/BCSNProject/bcgame-crash/">BCSNProject/bcgame-crash</a></p><img src="https://medium.com/_/stat?event=post.clientViewed&referrerSource=full_rss&postId=aeb6bd53e16e" width="1" height="1" alt="">]]></content:encoded>
